\end_inset

 In the housing bubble leading up to the crisis, house prices increased
 188% between 1997 and 2006 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "levitin2012explaining"

\end_inset

.
 Since land prices are a major component of housing prices, generally believed
 to reflect capitalized streams of ground rent, and, because land is much
 less easily produced than house structures, the prime candidate for the
 lion's share of house-price inflation is ground rent.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
A common misunderstanding of land is that, as a use value, it cannot be
 created but is instead an inherently limited 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

scarce resource
