 The the latter case, this particular computer software trope does not really
 work.
 The later period is more fragmented and a better analogy would be the marketing
 practices of a software manufacturer seeking to segment a market by building
 different versions of software on a common software base: a home version
 (alternative, non-capitalist economies), a media server version (cultural
 geographies), a server version (network geographies), etc.
