LatexCommand citep
after "320-321"
key "sheppard2011geographical"

\end_inset

.
 Economic geographers today reject most foundational assumptions and practices
 of mainstream and neoclassical economics.
 These include equilibrium, methodological individualism, reliance on solely
 mathematical models and quantitative methods, and treatment of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

the economy
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 as something separate from the rest of society.
 Instead, among economic geographers today there is a loose consensus that
 capitalism is conflictual, unstable, unable to permanently solve its own
 problems, generative of social and spatial inequality, one among many possible
 ways of providing for material human needs, and not superior to other systems.
 
\end_layout

