\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Capitalism's particularity
\bar default
 – economic systems have varied historically and geographically, and as
 a system of economic organization, capitalism is neither unique nor superior
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Disequilibrium and crises
\bar default
 – capitalism is inherently unstable, in perpetual disequilibrium, and crisis-pr
one, and its development is necessarily uneven and socioeconomically unequal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Totality and embeddedness
\bar default
 – the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

economy
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

