after "3"
key "Peck_2016_Macroeconomic"

\end_inset

, and it encompasses ecology and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

nature'; consequently, actual economic dynamics result from combinations
 of processes associated culture, politics, institutions, etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Spatiality matters
\bar default
 – space cannot legitimately be reduced to a Cartesian container of socioeconomi
c processes; instead, it is intrinsic to human life, and the spatial and
 material provisioning aspects of human social existence are dialectically
 co-constitutive
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Power matters
\bar default
 – society is not an undifferentiated collection of individuals, much less
 one with common goals and bound together by social contracts or other forms
 of mutual consent; instead it consists of social relations of unequal power
 various axes of domination/subordination, such as class, race, gender,
 and sexuality; conflict is endemic
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\bar under
Concreteness
\bar default
 – economic geography has a proclivity for concrete research on actual economics
 in specific places
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Notice though that these characteristics do not include any specific theories
 or methodologies.
 Furthermore, economic geography since the late 1980s is more commonly described
 by what it studies (localities, networks, etc.) rather than how it conducts
 research, what it has learned, what its major unanswered questions are,
 or what it hopes to learn.
